 research on Melanchthon’s role in Reformation history, but beyond this, reveals his importance in intellectual history as a universal scholar of the 16th century.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Aug 2020) 4aHumanism. 4aHumanismus. 4aMelanchthon, Philipp. 4aReformation. 70(DE-588)4045791-60(DE-627)1062002590(DE-576)209066873aPhilosophie2gnd 70(DE-588)4048946-20(DE-627)1043641650(DE-576)209079851aReformation2gnd 70(DE-588)4049716-10(DE-627)1046751520(DE-576)209083182aRezeption2gnd 70(DE-588)4059756-80(DE-627)1044520130(DE-576)209132140aTheologe2gnd 70(DE-588)4059758-10(DE-627)1041314460(DE-576)209132159aTheologie2gnd 7aRELIGION / Christianity / Lutheran.2bisacsh1 aFrank, Günter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLange, Axel08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2017z9783110548259oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruyterteBook-Paket Reformationz9783110551693oZDB-23-FJR0 cEPUBz97831103892650 cprintz978311033505740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311033580440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110335804423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110335804.jpg  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2017  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-FJR